{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SpotLight3D"]]},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/spotlight3d\/spotattenuation"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"spotAttenuation","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0.0"},{"type":"text","text":" will maintain a constant brightness through most of the range, but smoothly attenuate the light at the edge of the range. Use a value of "},{"code":"2.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for physically accurate lights as it results in the proper inverse square attenutation."}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Setting attenuation to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2.0"},{"type":"text","text":" or higher may result in distant objects receiving minimal light, even within range. For example, with a range of "},{"code":"4096","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", an object at "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"100"},{"type":"text","text":" units is attenuated by a factor of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0.0001"},{"text":". With a default brightness of ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the light would not be visible at that distance.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using negative or values higher than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"10.0"},{"text":" may lead to unexpected results.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SpotLight3D\/spotAttenuation"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls the distance attenuation function for spotlights."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot11SpotLight3DC15spotAttenuationSdvp","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"spotAttenuation","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"spotAttenuation","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/SpotLight3D":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SpotLight3D","title":"SpotLight3D","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/spotlight3d","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SpotLight3D","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpotLight3D"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A spotlight, such as a reflector spotlight or a lantern."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/SpotLight3D/spotAttenuation":{"title":"spotAttenuation","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Controls the distance attenuation function for spotlights.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"spotAttenuation","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"do